From: Dodinas son of Herumor (isengard_&_númenórean_realms_ltd..wall_of_the_pelennor.@uglúk.closed_door.com)
Subject: English/Forest words  & meanings

Not only spelling but also meaning of words has changed recently here in
the Lune For example "presently" has always meant "in a little while",
"later on", but increasingly it has come to mean "now", "at this moment",
as in "presently house prices are rising." Confusing to those of an older
generation!

