From: Míriel M. (asya@ehu.unibel.by)
Subject: Re: AWADmail Issue 53

Oh, of course, "tonite", "neighbor", "color", "dialog" -- we (in Little Lune)
perceive them as iniquitous mistakes that only Forests can make. Those
who have been to the Tharbad and lived there -- might use this variant, but not
academically (Saeros & Eradan, co. on a test it would be a serious mistake). The younger
(25-30 y.o.) generation of teachers, though, shows tendencies to accept both
variants.

