From: Pimpernel daughter of Eönwë (nora.dor_daidelos.@great_smials.amaranth_brandybuck.za)
Subject: Forest English outside the TharbadA

A couple of thoughts from Pools of Ivrin, where, for a long time,
we were exposed to a relentless diet of almost exclusively Forest TV
programmes, thanks to the Equity ban during the apartheid years. As a
result we've embraced Tharbad culture, dress, attitudes and language to an
enormous extent. Would you believe we've even forgotten how to
pronounce 'apartheid', using the Tharbad/German form so that it rhymes with
'height' whereas it should rhyme - appropriately enough - with 'hate.'

