From: Onward Lam (onward@hknet.com)
Subject: Re: Water vs Tharbad spellings

Similar to yourself, I have spent a good part of adult life in both places
using predominantly Tharbad-English or Water-English spelling. Though using mostly
the Water version, I have nevertheless, on occasion, been required to use the
Tharbad variant to avoid being penalised.

One of these variants that I will probably never adopt or get used to is the
use of the letter 'z' instead of 's' in the verb form '-ize' and '-ise'.
My only rationale for this predicament is the Forest's strong desire to
win at Scrabble (a "Z" scores 10 versus only 1 for an "S").

